The results reported in this work were produced under two explicitly defined pipeline configurations that differ only in the pre-pruning of candidate similarity edges prior to graph construction.

The full candidate graph configuration uses the complete set of cross-species candidate edges generated by the k-mer similarity stage. The Jaccard-pruned graph configuration applies an additional pre-pruning step that retains only high-confidence similarity edges based on Jaccard similarity thresholds and per-node degree caps, substantially reducing graph density.

All downstream processing steps — including robust z-score normalization, component construction, structural feature computation, and candidate ranking — are identical across configurations.

The pipeline supports both configurations deterministically via explicit input edge files (candidates.tsv for the full graph and pruned_edge_jaccard.tsv for the pruned graph), ensuring full reproducibility of all reported results.
Reproducibility and configurations
The results reported in this work were produced under two explicitly defined pipeline configurations that differ only in the pre-pruning of candidate similarity edges prior to graph construction. The full candidate graph configuration uses the complete set of cross-species candidate edges generated by the k-mer similarity stage. The Jaccard-pruned graph configuration applies an additional pre-pruning step that retains only high-confidence similarity edges based on Jaccard similarity thresholds and per-node degree caps, substantially reducing graph density. All downstream processing steps — including robust z-score normalization, component construction, structural feature computation, and candidate ranking — are identical across configurations. The pipeline supports both configurations deterministically via explicit input edge files (candidates.tsv for the full graph and pruned_edge_jaccard.tsv for the pruned graph), ensuring full reproducibility of all reported results.